properties.sfomuseum:description: Stock certificate issued to New York & Buenos Aires Line, Inc. for 400 shares of Aviation Corporation of the Americas; certificate number 45, dated November 1, 1930; orange and white; official corporate seal impression with original signatures of E. S. (Sally) Swaggerty, Assistant Secretary, and C. V. Whitney, President; signed on reverse with indication of stock transfer power “on file” signed by M. Shearer; countersigned by The Chase National Bank of the City of New York (overprinting The Equitable Trust Company of New York), registered November 1, 1930 by The New York Trust Company; certificate note by American Bank Note Company; document defaced by hole punch cancellation at left and lower right.
